column1: SIT3 || Retail || Facing issue with MultiSimSwap for Stone Tariff New Acq scenario.
column30:
Hi Team

We tested a order with the following condition:

 
|*Channel*|RETAIL|
|*MainCard SimType(with esim push)*|eSIM|
|*UltraCard SimType(with esim push Stone tariff)*|eSIM|
|*MainCard Activity*|NEW ACQ|

 

But SimSwap request is failing for the Ultracard eSim with the following error:

EXT Map: {Street=Singerstr., {*}OrderLineId=1398990{*}, OrderStatus=OrderInProgressNoFailure, HouseNumber=109, LineOfBusiness=Mobile_Postpaid, MarketingCode=BRI, ResumeOrderInd=Y, OrderLineScenario=NEW, AdvertisingCode=INB, OrderLineStatus=InProgress-SubmittedToBackend, CustomerType=PRIVATE, BAN=DE60100700240928226000, TargetCustomerId=20189334, UniquePackageID=37739/2, TicketType=Fallout, contactPerson=, [CustomerEmail=Anurag@mail.com|mailto:CustomerEmail=Anurag@mail.com], CustomerName=AnuRag, GeneralTransactionID=718754240, VOID=40696179, {*}Channel=retail{*}, CustomerAddressCity=Berlin, ErrorCode=EAI003236, AgentDetails=7:Super Agent, CampaignCode=MGM, *ErrorDescription=An error was encountered while invoking KIAS-RequestSimSwap WS. Details [Error_Code: EAI003236, Error_Message: New sim number field should not be empty while immediate sim swap requested.,* Error_Type: {*}Functional{*}, Error_Sevirity: E, *Error_Information:  New sim number field should not be empty while immediate sim swap requested., Backend Error Code: 1369]  ,* SourceSubChannel=HE, CustomerTelephoneNumber=017978945612, ProcessId={*}136795742{*}, {*}SubscriberNumber=1629910484{*}, CustomerAddressZip=10179, ErrorCategory=Business, {*}OmniusOrderId=37739{*}, SourceSystemName={*}OGW{*}, {*}ServiceName=RequestSimSwap{*}, {*}OmniusOrderLineId=2{*}, SOC=DUM_ACTFE:ADD|SX_TEL:ADD|SO_PSMS:ADD|SO_RO:ADD|SO_CSD:ADD|SO_GP:ADD|SO_PTELKW:ADD|shippingf:ADD, ToTariff=CIOT2FH10, TargetSystemName=Mobile_Postpaid}

DTM Map: {}

 

Steps:
 # Login to Retail channel.
 # Add a Mobile package.
 # Add HW , tariff and oneNr. For oderline 1.
 # Add Stone Tariff and optionen (with Onenumber as eSIM) for orderline 2.
 # Add hw (smartwatch) to Stone Tariff.
 # Proceed to checkout...Fill all necessary details
 # Select the SimType as eSIM (for main tariff) and enable eSIM-Push.
 # Select the main tariff, that was booked in the configurator for smartwatch
 # Select The Ultracard SimType as eSIM (with eSIM-Push)
 # Select address as Ship to Store.
 # Validate IBAN...Submit the Order...Verify OGW logs
 # Verify that the Sim (for main tariff and for onenumber ( = Ultracard)) should be picked from OGW_VIRTUAL_SIM table. Note: For activation of STONE a dedicated pool of virtual SIMs will be used. These virtual SIMs are not swappable.
 # Verify that all the subscribers should be activated in KIAS.
 # Verify that sharp SIMSWAP should be triggered right after activation of eSIM main tariff
 # Verify that Email 5910 or Email 5930 should be invoked for Mainsim (depending on eMail-address verification status)
 # Verify that MultiSIMSWAP should be triggered right after activation of eSIM Ultracard.
 # Verify that Email 5910 only should be invoked for ultracard eSIM.
 # Verify that MultiSIM should be booked through ActivateSubscriber at the time of Activation.
 # Verify that order get the Status "Imported to VORAS"
 # Verify the order get the Status "VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_HANDOUT"(EID + OGWOrderID + OrderlineID) status.
 # Verify that GeteSIMInformation should be triggered for your subscriberNo (main tariff). Note: Based on the response, OGW needs to check the status of the eSIM for tariff option onenumber first. If eSIM-status is "ready for download without EID",
 # Verify that MaintainEID should be triggered for your order.
 # Verify that OGW set order-status to "Completed-Success" after after EVT_040 is received.

 

Actual Result: Multisimswap is failing for eSIM Ultracard.

Expected Result : Multisimswap should success for eSIM Ultracard.

 

PFA logs for reference.

column1: SIT3 || Retail || RequestSimSwapRequest is not being called for the MainCard for Prolongation scenarios
column30:
We’ve tested the flow (with below mentioned conditions), and we’ve encountered that the RequestSimSwapRequest is not being called for the MainCard :

Channel: RETAIL
MainCard SimType(with esim push): eSIM 
UltraCard SimType(with psim: pSIM
MainCard Activity: Prolongation

Steps:
1. Login to Retail channel…Perform legacy search on the customer…Load the customer. 
2. Check Eligibility for customer VVL. 
3. Click on Standard Prolongation option. 
4. Add new Tariff and optionen (with OneNumber (pSIM)). 
5. Proceed to checkout. Fill all the necessary details. 
6. Select the SimType (for main tariff) as eSIM and enable eSIM-Push .
7. Select The Ultracard SimType as PhysicalSim. 
8. Submit the Order. Verify OGW logs. 
9. Verify that the manual inserted SIMSerialNr for booking OneNr should be used for activation. 
10. Verify that all the subscribers should be activated in KIAS 
11. Verify that unsharp SIMSWAP should be triggered. 
12. Verify that Email 5910 or Email 5930 should be invoked for Mainsim .
13. Verify that, InProgress-HWFulfilmentReady status should be received for orderline. 
14. Verify that GeteSIMInformation should be triggered for your subscriberNo. 
15. Verify that MaintainEID should be triggered for your order.
16. Verify that OGW set order-status should be “Completed-Success” .

Actual Result: RequestSimSwapRequest is not being called for the MainCard SimType
Expected Result: RequestSimSwapRequest should be called for the MainCard SimType

OGW Order Id: 3559467

PFA logs for reference.
column560: The OGW team fixed the code and provided the new fix. In build 7638, it's working fine.
column1211: 28/Aug/25 1:41 PM;anurag.vaid@vodafone.com;OGW Team is checking this issue.;;;

column1213: 02/Sep/25 1:55 PM;anurag.vaid@vodafone.com;There is still no Simswap for MainCard.;;;
column1214: 09/Sep/25 1:39 PM;anurag.vaid@vodafone.com;Currently Retesting in SIT2 env, but retest is blocked due to OS-77331;;;
column1215: 17/Sep/25 4:23 PM;anurag.vaid@vodafone.com;The OGW team fixed the code and provided the new fix. In build 7638, it's working fine. ;;;

These are the new logs  [^462111_WS.xml];;;
column1212:
18/Jul/25 11:01 AM;shruti.kanchan@vodafone.com;Hi All,
 
As discussed during the call with Jan, Andrey, Anurag, Abhishek, and Pallavi, I’d like to reiterate the following clarification:
 
Jan confirmed that for ILS scenarios - where there is no change in hardware and the ILS changes pertain only to tariff, options, and discounts, there is no separate requirement to generate a DF contract document.
 
Omnius indicates Device Financing related submit parameters only when there is a selection of a DFP Device SKU.
 
The mobile contract generation will continue to follow the business-as-usual process. Therefore, the SubmitOrder from OIL to OGW will not include the MobileContractDocumentforDF parameters, as there is no hardware or shipping amount that needs to be excluded.
 
@Pallavi The previous PriceInfo tag seen in ILS scenario was invalid (separate defect which is now closed), I believe this fix was already delivered. 
 
Thank you,
Shruti

column1: SIT-5 || Sanity || Carrier ident Delivery Option
column30:
Hello Bharath,

 

When we are triggering new mobile ACQ Telesales in SIT-5 we are blocked on Delivery option when we select Carrier Ident.

We noticed that Standard Liefertermin option is missing when we select Carrier Ident. Hence the weiter button is disabled.

Could you please check and update us.

 

Carrier Ident

!image-2025-05-16-16-11-53-113.png|width=1227,height=646!

 

Online Ident Method is showing Standar Liefertermin option and we can continue with order normally.

 

!image-2025-05-16-16-12-09-271.png!
column560: We have retested and issue was resolved.
column1211:
19/May/25 11:06 AM;bharath.krishnamurthy@vodafone.com;[~charalambos.stylianou@vodafone.com] 

 
Irina 
 
added a comment -
 
 
Hi Charalambos ,

I`ve made some Archive log analysis. Let me share the observations.
I believe that the Standard Liefertermin option depends upon StandardDeliveryIndicator field value in GetAvailableShippingOptions response.
I analyzed these two cases, Archive logs (I chose Archive based on screenshot time).
For DHL, we have several AvailableShippingOptionsDetails sections, one of which consists of

*<StandardDeliveryIndicator>true</StandardDeliveryIndicator>*

For blocking case we have only one AvailableShippingOptionsDetails section with

*<StandardDeliveryIndicator>false</StandardDeliveryIndicator>*

Could you please  ask OGW team to make the appropriate changes (set this Indicator as true for failed case) to check on SIT.;;;

Thanks;;;

Irina 
 
added a comment -
 
Hi Harsh/Charalambos,
 
OIL passes on what it receives from OGW unconditionally. OSE disables the button based on the response. Initially, OGW sends this value as false.
I found several related stories



I`m not sure what is the latest logic. It is better to check with BA from your side and any new requirements has come on this, please share the user story details for reference;;;

column1: SIT 1 || Retail || OGW is missing some information in the PushOrderStatus request for D2C Migcoc scenario
column30:
Hi OGW team

We tried testing a D2C scenario in the retail channel.

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to Retail channel.
 # Search and load a debit customer.
 # Perform D2C.
 # Fill all the necessary details.
 # Select Ship to store option.
 # Validate IBAN.
 # Generate Documents.

Expected Result: Order should completed successfully.

Actual Result:  *There is missing some information in the PushOrderStatus request after getting VORAS_FINAL_SUCCESS_SHIP_TO_STORE_HANDOUT status from VORAS.*

 ** 

If we trigger HW-fulfillment-ready status using SOAPUI after that PushorderStatus, The LoanActivation service is triggered twice which results in the following error:


*ErrorDescription=[HTTPAdaptor] Can not connect to HTTP Server[dxl-preprod.rat-hub.citt.connect-vf.de:-1], Status[422], Message[\{\"code\":\"422 UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY\",\"reason\":\"Invalid state transition RequestedActivation to RequestedActivation\",\"message\":\"Invalid state transition RequestedActivation to RequestedActivation\",\"status\":\"UNPROCESSABLE_ENTITY\"}],*

 ** 

So Could you please check the PushOrderStatus request.

Also PFA logs and PushOrderStatus request.

column1: SIT1 | Telesales | IdentMethod value is being sent as empty in LoanApplication request for VVL scenario
column30:
Wir haben versucht, das VVL-Szenario im Telesales-Kanal auszuführen, aber IdentMethod wird als none in Submit Order XML gesendet.

Und ich nehme an, das ist der Grund, warum wir es in der LoanApplication-Anfrage als leeres Attribut senden.

Infolgedessen schlägt die LoanApplication-Anfrage auf der GFP-Seite fehl.

Wie wir besprochen haben, können wir nicht sehen, dass diese Ident-Methode in der gegebenen User Story behandelt wird.

 

Empfehlen Sie uns: [https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-66445|https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOS-66445&data=05%7C02%7CSudhanshu.Shekhar%40amdocs.com%7Cbec417a590684228fad108dd871cb309%7Cc8eca3ca127646d59d9da0f2a028920f%7C0%7C0%7C638815279538393695%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=NkGXuySYbzA2FxUp05ZFTEAn1lBe%2Bzg8tj2syG6dzwY%3D&reserved=0]

 

Bitte prüfen und beraten.

 

*Schritte zum Reproduzieren:*
 # Melden Sie sich beim Telesales-Kanal an.
 # Suchen und laden Sie einen VVL-berechtigten Kunden mit ausländischer Adresse.
 # Führen Sie die VVL-Prüfung durch.
 # Führen Sie eine Standardverlängerung durch.
 # DF-Tarif und HW hinzufügen
 # Zur Kasse gehen
 # Senden Sie die Bestellung ab

 

Erwartetes Ergebnis: Die ident-Methode sollte als none gesendet werden

Tatsächliches Ergebnis: Die Ident-Methode wird in den Erfüllungsprotokollen als Keine eingetragen

column1: SIT1 | Error after clicking the contract extension button for VVL Customers with foreign addresses
column30:
We are currently validating the scenario where the DF portfolio should not be offered to existing customers with foreign addresses during VVL.

You can find the related Jira ticket here: OS-54821.

We can perform a VVL check for customers with foreign addresses. However, we encounter errors when attempting to proceed with VVL (Standard prolongation).

Initially, we receive a 500 Internal Server Error. Upon retrying, we get the following error message:

 

*Error:* “This product has already been changed in your shopping cart. Please empty your shopping cart first.”

 

Notably, there are no products in the shopping cart.

 

Could you please investigate this issue? Attached are the test results for your reference.

{*}Test Data{*}: 20112151

*Steps to Reproduce:*
 # Log in to the Telesales/Retail channel.
 # Search for and load a VVL-eligible customer with a foreign address.
 # Perform the VVL check.
 # After the VVL check passes, try to Standard prolongation.
 #  

*Expected Result:* The agent should be able to access the configurator page to perform VVL. 

*Actual Result:* Omnius throws an error after clicking the contract extension button.

 * Denied Denial 0 --> "denialReasonCode" = 0

 * ZINIA_DN_IDENTITY_REJECT
 * ZINIA-DN-IDENTITY-REJECT

 * Denied Denial 1 --> "denialReasonCode" = 1

 * ZINIA_DN_CREDIT_REJECT
 * ZINIA-DN-CREDIT-REJECT

 * Denied Denial 2 --> "denialReasonCode" = 2

 * ZINIA_DN_IP_REJECT
 * ZINIA-DN-IP-REJECT

 * Denied Denial 3 --> "denialReasonCode" = 3

 * ZINIA_DN_CREDIT_IP_REJECT
 * ZINIA-DN-CREDIT-IP-REJECT

 * Denied Pending --> No "denialReasonCode"

 * ZINIA_DN_PENDING
 * ZINIA-DN-PENDING

 

Otherwise, the loan could be rejected.

 

So we need to first check with omnius team regarding the lastname.;;;

column1: SIT1 | Omnius not showing an option to cancel the pre-order package
column30:
We tried submitting a DF order in telesales channel with DF tariff and pre-order HW and order is not yet completed.

As per business user story https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-55738, If a pre-order package is being cancelled from Omnius as a result OGW should also cancel the DF Loan application process.

We tried following the steps mentioned in the business user story but  we couldn’t find an option to cancel the pre-order package in Omnius.

Could you please check and suggest where we can find an option to cancel this package.

Also, please let us know if we have any permission or any other approach we need to follow.

 

 

*Steps to reproduce:*

 
 # Login to telesales channel
 # Select a Mobile package
 # Add DF tariff and Pre-order HW
 # Move to checkout
 # Submit the order.
 # Load the order using order is in omnius

 

*Expected Result:* Omnius should show an option to cancel the pre-order package.

*Actual Result:* We can’t find an option to cancel the pre-order package.

Hello All,

*Please find below MOM:*

BUSINESS-WP1: As a sales agent I want be able to Cancel the Pre-Order package from Omnius and as a result, to cancel the DF Loan application process.

 
 * {*}Telesales{*}: Only after successful online identification does OGW start the LoanApplication process.

And we don’t have possibility to cancel an Omnius pre-order package after the online Identification has passed.

We discussed it with [@Robert|mailto:Robert.Goebbels@Vodafone.com] [@Shruti|mailto:Shruti.Kanchan@TechMahindra.com] and omnius colleagues, however once LoanApplication is initiated, there is no method to cancel a pre-order package from Omnius.

 
 * *Retail:* We don’t have this possibility of cancelling a pre-order package from Omnius in Retail channel.

Although [@Shruti|mailto:Shruti.Kanchan@TechMahindra.com] will check once again and confirm.

 
 * After all of these discussions, we were unable to determine how an agent may cancel a pre-order in accordance with the business story's scenario.

This appears to be a design gap that requires attention.;;;

column1227:
25/Apr/25 1:20 PM;horst.froehlich3@vodafone.com;After discussion with [~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com] we can close this defect because it cannot be tested.
Details for that from Rob as follow.

Only open task ist the {color:#de350b}+*TODO*+{color} at the end of this comment.
[~robert.goebbels@vodafone.com] - Could you please check who should clarify this task and create a new Delivery Task for the Epic with detailed description and assigned to relevant responsible.

*Rob Göbbels AFTER meeting with TechM/Amdocs/ Int Tester Sudhanshu:*
This story is cancelled after all:
REASON:
IS SITUATION (assuming the PCAT would be configured, so that Hardware is defined as Pre-Order hardware) only if the PRE-ORDER is still in the status : "pending online-ident"  this pre-order can be cancelled. We do not know if this is a bug or a feature, but:
 # it is not as we (designteam3) had expected/  had understood the is situation
 # assuming that  it is a defect/designGap:  then this is NO DeviceFinancing issue, but a production defect.

This means however, that this use-case as described here, is obsolete (for now)
 # first of all:  with the current PCAT configuration in production, the pre-sales use- will not happen
 # second:  even if at some point in time VF decides to re-activate the pre-order functionality in OSF, even then this use-case will not take place until this functionality is changed (change-request)

-> it makes no sense to invest time in integration / acc test for this businss story 
->  business stroy has been cancelled

*Logname : CSACTIVDMN_CSACTIVDMN_MMC_20250404_090344.log*
column560:
Root cause:-

In the private_bin directory, there's a private_profile. This one redefines the TUXDIR to Tuxedo 10 and puts the corresponding library path into LD_LIBRARY_PATH. So, the daemon uses the wrong Tuxedo library. With this library, the daemon process is not able to read the configuration file from Tuxedo 12. So, the Tuxedo call fails.

Solution:

Remove the TUXDIR setting and the connected change to LD_LIBRARY_PATH from private_profile, and after re-login and restart of the daemon, the call will succeed.
column1211: 07/Apr/25 1:14 PM;anurag.vaid@vodafone.com;The KIAS Infra team is currently investigating the issue.;;;
column1212:
08/Apr/25 3:29 PM;gaurav.chauhan4@vodafone.com;After correcting private_profile, it worked. 

*Root cause:-*

In the private_bin directory, there's a private_profile. This one redefines the TUXDIR to Tuxedo 10 and puts the corresponding library path into LD_LIBRARY_PATH. So, the daemon uses the wrong Tuxedo library. With this library, the daemon process is not able to read the configuration file from Tuxedo 12. So, the Tuxedo call fails.

 

*Solution:*

Remove the TUXDIR setting and the connected change to LD_LIBRARY_PATH from private_profile, and after re-login and restart of the daemon, the call will succeed.

can you please share here the sos request from Omnius?
also the ogw order id.
from the DB, i found this OGWOrder id: 8976135
is that your order?
if yes, ou are sending the wrong set order status from Omnius.
according to drools, when sending Completed-HWFulfillmentFailed you also need to send these values as well:

column1: SIT1 | GetEsimInformation and MaintainEID is being triggered twice
column30:
I tried running New ACQ scenario in Retail and Telesales both the channels  where email is also being triggered towards OM.

However we observed that GetEsimInformation and MaintainEID is being triggered twice.

Could you please check?

PFA logs for your reference.

 

Retail OGWOrderID: 8976150

Telesales OGWOrderID: 8976110
column560:
Seems to be some temporary issue. Retested again and it works. Got the clarification from OGW BA and Dev. So closing the defect. 




Dev Comments:-

I can see that it is being called twice because one from setorder status and another as part of email validation .

Please refer this US :
https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-49625 , according to this  getesimInformation should get called after Email-Validation-Success also.

And MaintainEID only Once.

So it looks like an expected behaviour.
column1211:
03/Apr/25 2:50 PM;gaurav.chauhan4@vodafone.com;Seems to be some temporary issue. Retested again and it works. Got the clarification from OGW BA and Dev. So closing the defect.

[https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-49625|https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fjira.sp.vodafone.com%2Fbrowse%2FOS-49625&data=05%7C02%7CGaurav.Chauhan%40amdocs.com%7Cb7e34c8003da41ae9c8608dd71c552fa%7Cc8eca3ca127646d59d9da0f2a028920f%7C0%7C0%7C638791814493219712%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=si6Qh0o9ct3YA773VpmMG3uLYkQNhaN9Yr%2F8GVzsYZc%3D&reserved=0] , according to this  getesimInformation should get called after Email-Validation-Success also.

                }

"contactType": ""

contact type is OGW issue, and we have a fix for it.
locationType is missing from the submit request so its empty.

column1: SIT1 || Telesales || Getting Same Red Banner For All The Email Categories
column30:
We are trying to execute epic  OS-28388, wherein we are getting the same red banner for all the email categories.

 !image-2025-03-26-15-10-20-443.png|thumbnail! 

Steps to reproduce:
Precondition: Switch is implemented to enable or disable the Epic functionalities.
1. Login to Omnius Telesales.
2. Agent has the permission (Solstice_ACQ) to service new solstice customer.
3. Verify the Service Availability check for the address and Solstice products are available for the given service address.
4. Select “Solstice Festnetz Angebote” option to load solstice products in configurator.
5. Verify there should be product(s) in the Shopping Cart from the loaded products in Configurator.
6. Verify Usecase Identification, PackageType (as %solstice), Segment and Channel combination exist in the configuration table.
7. Move to to the Checkout by clicking on “Zum Checkout”.
8. Fill all the required details in Kundennamen.
9. Enter the email address under “Kontaktdaten” section.

Expected Result: Email address should be validated and based on which it will show different banners.
Actual Result: Email address is validated and it is showing the same red banner for all the email categories.

column560: It was found that the queue [eaiGtCstBan] was not defined in the sync EMS scripts. The queue has been added, and the sync component has been restarted.
column1211:

It was found that the queue [eaiGtCstBan] was not defined in the sync EMS scripts. The queue has been added, and the sync component has been restarted. The issue is now resolved, and it's working fine now.;;;

column1: SIT1 | Omnius Ordermanager page not reflecting the correct order status for DFP orders
column30:
Hello Omnius Team,

 

We tried running one Retail New ACQ order with DF tariff and HW in SIT1 but it got failed with status *Completed-RejectedByGFP.*

However omnius is not updating the correct status in order manager page.

 

As per Business US https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-58114 and omnius US: https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/OS-60867.
 * Omnius Ordermanager must reflect the orderline status to '{*}Fehlgeslagen'{*}
 * Omnius Ordermanager must reflect a new message “ *Geräte-Ratenzahlung abgelehnt* “ in the {*}BestellInformation section{*}.

 

Could you please check?

 

PFA PushOrderStatus logs for your reference.

 

*Steps to reproduce:*
 # Login to Retail channel
 # Add a mobile package
 # Select DF tariff and HW
 # Move to checkout
 # Fill all the request details
 # Submit the order
 # Order should fail with status Completed-RejectedByGFP.

 

*Expected Result:* Omnius should reflect the correct orderline status on order manager as mentioned in the US .

 

{*}Actual Result{*}: Omnius is showing order line status as *IN DER ERSTEN WARTESCHLANGE* in order manager and no new section for  {*}Details Ergänzungen{*}.

column1: SIT1 || Telesales || DXL 'emailValidation' Service Is Not Being Called
column30:
We are trying to execute epic OS-28388, wherein the dxl service (emailValidation) is not called, for the flow where ‘Email is not Unique’. 

Steps to reproduce:
Precondition: Switch is implemented as mentioned in OS-61399 to enable or disable the Epic functionalities.

2.	Agent has the permission (Solstice_ACQ) to service new solstice customer.
3.	Verify the Service Availability check for the address and Solstice products are available for the given service address.
4.	Select “Solstice Festnetz Angebote” option to load solstice products in configurator.
5.	Verify there should be product(s) in the Shopping Cart from the loaded products in Configurator.
6.	Verify Usecase Identification, PackageType (as %solstice), Segment and Channel combination exist in the configuration table.  
7.	Move to to the Checkout by clicking on “Zum Checkout”.
8.	Fill all the required details in Kundennamen.
9.	Enter the email address under “Kontaktdaten” section.
10.	Verify DXL(emailValidation) service should be called. 

Expected Result: DXL ‘emailValidation’ service should be called.
Actual Result: DXL ‘emailValidation’ service is not being called.

column1: SIT 1 || Telesales || Weiter button is disabled on checkout Page for DF tariff and Hardware options.
column30:
Hi Omnius Team,

We are unable to proceed with the order submission with *DF tariff and Hardware* in *telesales in SIT 1* env because *the Weiter button is disabled* on the checkout page, as it recognizes the German address as a foreign address.

Steps to reproduce:
 # Login to Telesales channel.
 # Search and load a debit customer.
 # Select Debit to Credit Option.
 # Then add {*}DF tariff and Hardware{*}.
 # Then proceed to checkout.
 # Fill the required details and click on *Weiter* button.

 

*Expected Result:* Weiter button should be enabled after filling all the details.

*Actual Result:* Weiter button is disabled after filling all the details.

Verify, OGW should Always populate SubscriberNumber as phoneNumber in LoanActivation API call "49""$(SubscriberNumber)"
